('Question #111', 'Which of the following describes the characteristics of a Boot Sector Virus?<br>', '                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"A\">                                                                  A.                                                              </span>                                                                                                                    Modifies directory table entries so that directory entries point to the virus code instead of the actual program.                                                      </li>                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"B\">                                                                  B.                                                              </span>                                                                                                                    Moves the MBR to another location on the RAM and copies itself to the original location of the MBR.                                                      </li>                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item correct-hidden\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"C\">                                                                  C.                           