('Question #225', 'While testing a web application in development, you notice that the web server does not properly ignore the `dot dot slash` (../) character string and instead returns the file listing of a folder higher up in the folder structure of the server.<br>What kind of attack is possible in this scenario?<br>', '                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"A\">                                                                  A.                                                              </span>                                                                                                                    Cross-site scripting                                                      </li>                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"B\">                                                                  B.                                                              </span>                                                                                                                    SQL injection                                                      </li>                                                                                                        <li class=\"multi-choice-item\">                                                                                                                        <span class=\"multi-choice-letter\" data-choice-letter=\"C\">                                                                  C.